Manchester City lost 4-2 to Manchester United in the Premier League on Sunday . 
  Sergio Aguero has scored 100 goals in 158 games for City this season . 
  Manuel Pellegrini faces a battle to keep his star man at the Etihad Stadium . 
  Real Madrid and Barcelona are interested in the Argentine . 
  City could lose Aguero if they slip out of the top four . 
  The club are reportedly targeting Paul Pogba and Raheem Sterling . 
 